1-1. For year 2021 only, calculate and report the summary statistics for the number of days inventory in stock, including min, mean, median, max, and standard deviation for the nine business sectors (see below);

Tip #1: you need to use year 2020 data to obtain the beginning inventory for year 2021 for each firm;

Tip #2: you need to extract the first two-digits from the 4-digit SIC code in order to define the business sectors (A. Agriculture, Forestry, & Fishing; B. Mining; C. Construction; D. Manufacturing; E. Transportation & Public Utilities; F. Wholesale Trade; G. Retail Trade; H. Finance, Insurance, & Real Estate; I. Services). Details of the sector classification is available at https://mckimmoncenter.ncsu.edu/2digitsiccodes-2/

Tip #3: some business sectors may not have inventory. If so, you can simply drop them from your analyses (in a single graph). 

1-2. Plot the min, median, and max number of days inventory in stock for the above nine business sectors; 

Tell me the way to do this in excel using any function/formula, I understand you do not have the exact Excel file, so you do not need to give me the answer, just tell me the way to do it, thank you so much.
